node.text:
Postcards from Turkey 🍃 Have you ever been to this beautiful country before?

Turkey has 44 National Parks that look after its stunning natural heritage – so if you decide to visit, you’ll have plenty of options to choose from (some of our favorites are the Yedigoller National Park and the Saklikent Milli Park). 🌳🇹🇷

Tag a @nature lover! 😍

📷 @cumacevikphoto #nature
📍Turkey

node.text:
The world's deepest pool in Dubai with @_theexpeditioner - It is 60 meters deep 🤯

Opened in July 2021, featuring a depth of 60 meters and 14 million liters of warm water, the equivalent of six Olympic-sized swimming pools. The attraction offers a variety of options for both novice and proffesionals divers alike, such as scuba dives, freedives, diving courses, and workshops for all levels. 🏊

Deep Dive Dubai has posted a notice on its website for those planning to visit the city's famed Burj Khalifa afterward: "Don't visit the top of the skyscraper after diving. After any dive, it's recommended to wait 18-24 hours before ascending higher than 300 meters (1,000 feet). However, there is no risk in diving after having visited the tallest building in the world."

Would you take the plunge and dive into this underwater world? 💦

📽 @_theexpeditioner #nature
📍 Deep Dive Dubai
🎶 Fousheé - Deep End

node.text:
Beautiful glass house surrounded by @nature 🍃Tag someone you'd spend a night here with 🖤

Located 700 km (435 miles) north of Bangkok, Chiang Mai is nestled in a verdant valley on the banks of the Ping River. A land of misty mountains and colourful hill tribes, a playground for seasoned travellers, a paradise for shoppers and a delight for adventurers. On a trip to Chiang Mai, the curious traveller can expand their horizons with Thai massage and cooking courses. Others will be bowled over by the variety of handicrafts and antiques. The wild child will find plenty of lively nightlife, and the epicure can indulge in wonderful cuisine. Despite its relatively small size, Chiang Mai truly has it all.

📽 @sunny_rung #nature
📍 Chiang Mai, Thailand
🎶 Novo Amor - From Gold

node.text:
Sunset goals 💜 Cornwall is a county on England’s rugged southwestern tip. It forms a peninsula encompassing wild moorland and hundreds of sandy beaches, culminating at the promontory Land’s End. 

The south coast, dubbed the Cornish Riviera, is home to picturesque harbour villages such as Fowey and Falmouth. The north coast is lined with towering cliffs and seaside resorts like Newquay, known for surfing.

Where did you witness the most beautiful sunset you have ever seen? 🌅

📽 @liv_jaynex #nature
📍Cornwall, United Kingdom
🎶 Matt Hansen - Yellow

node.text:
Psychedelic Kelp Forest 🤯 (Trypophobia Warning!) “In ocean photography, low visibility is usually a bad thing. However, I was mesmerized by the kelp forests of Eland's Bay, as they shimmered in and out of view in the cloudy green surf. Eland's Bay is a beach town along South Africa's Atlantic coast, frequented by surfers, dolphins, and sea birds. 

One of the clips from this shoot went viral on TikTok. 30% of the commenters said that they enjoyed it, 30% said that it triggered their trypophobia, 10% thought the kelp looked like dementors from Harry Potter, and 20% said that it reminded them of the psychedelic visuals of an LSD/mushrooms trip 😂.”

What was your reaction when watching this? 🌊

📽 @skypacking #nature
📍Eland's Bay, South Africa
🎶 @sadnightdynamite - Psychedelic Views
